Defendant Sheila S Lott in court with attorney Carl W Chesshir.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Court takes recess for the defendant to read the criminal complaint.  Case recalled at 3:00 pm.   Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 4.  Court finds defendant guilty.

The Court Orders the Following:

Imposed and Stayed Sentence of:

4 Months  Huber (Credit - 1 day) HUBER WITH STANDARD RELEASE CONDITIONS.  Can be transferred to Kenosha County as long as it is served in the facility.

Term of Probation: 1 Year  Can be transferred to Kenosha County

Conditions of Probation:
- Maintain Contact with Dr. Hamilton;
- No Use or Possession of illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
- No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
- Any valid prescription drugs must be taken in the manner in which they are prescribed;
- Inform agent of all prescriptions;
- Sign Medical Release for Agent;
- Completed 25 hours of community service during the first 10 months or probation;
- Follow through with any recommendations by Agent;
- Take a Criminal Thinking Course;
- Operate a Motor Vehicle with a Valid Drivers License;
- Maintain/Obtain full time activity;
- No contact with Woodman's in Memonomee Falls.

Restitution:  $251.41 joint and several with co-defendants (To be paid at the rate of $25 per month commencing 8-1-14)

Costs: $ 253.00
DNA Surcharge:  $200.00
(To to be paid as a condition of  probation at the rate of $25.00  per month commencing 8-1-14; alternate 46 hours of community service to be completed by end of probation.   Court must receive notice of completion prior to due date.)
